Title: [webapps] Angular-Base64-Upload Library 0.1.21 - Unauthenticated Remote Code Execution (RCE)
Summary Impact: The Angular-Base64-Upload Library 0.1.21 unauthenticated remote code execution vulnerability allows attackers to execute arbitrary code remotely without authentication, potentially leading to full system compromise, data theft, and disruption of services.
Key IOCs: 
Mitigations: Patch vulnerable Angular-Base64-Upload Library versions, Restrict unauthenticated access to upload functionalities, Use runtime application self-protection (RASP) tools, Employ network segmentation to limit exposure, Regularly update and audit third-party libraries
TTPs: T1190 - Exploit Public-Facing Application, T1059 - Command and Scripting Interpreter
Attack Vectors: Unauthenticated remote code execution via web application upload functionality
Tools: 
Malware: 
Historical Context: Similar vulnerabilities in web applications such as compop.ca 3.5.3 and Langflow 1.3.0 have allowed attackers to execute arbitrary code remotely, leading to full system compromise and data theft. These incidents highlight the critical risk posed by unauthenticated remote code execution vulnerabilities in widely used libraries and applications.

Title: SonicWall Patches 3 Flaws in SMA 100 Devices Allowing Attackers to Run Code as Root
Summary Impact: The vulnerabilities in SonicWall SMA 100 devices could allow remote authenticated attackers to bypass security checks, delete files, and execute code with root privileges, potentially leading to full system compromise and unauthorized access to sensitive data.
Key IOCs: CVE-2025-32819, Remote authenticated attacker with SSL-VPN user privileges, Path traversal bypass attempts, Unauthorized deletion of files on SMA 100 devices
Mitigations: Patch management and timely updates, Access control enforcement on VPN users, Network segmentation to isolate SMA devices, Continuous monitoring and alerting for suspicious activity, User privilege auditing and minimization
TTPs: T1190 - Exploit Public-Facing Application, T1078 - Valid Accounts, T1210 - Exploitation of Remote Services
Attack Vectors: SSL-VPN authentication, Remote code execution via path traversal
Tools: 
Malware: 
Historical Context: Similar to previous critical vulnerabilities in remote access appliances, these flaws allow remote authenticated attackers to execute code as root, posing significant risks to enterprise network security and data integrity.

Title: New 'Defendnot' tool tricks Windows into disabling Microsoft Defender
Summary Impact: The Defendnot tool poses a significant risk by disabling essential security features, leaving systems vulnerable to further attacks.
Key IOCs: Defendnot tool executable, Registry keys related to fake antivirus registration, Event logs showing Microsoft Defender being disabled unexpectedly
Mitigations: Regularly audit security software status on endpoints., Restrict administrative privileges to trusted personnel only., Deploy behavioral analytics to detect tampering with security tools., Enable tamper protection features in Microsoft Defender.
TTPs: T1562.001 - Impair Defenses: Disable or Modify Tools, T1089 - Disabling Security Tools
Attack Vectors: Malicious software execution, Social engineering to deploy tool
Tools: Defendnot
Malware: 
Historical Context: Similar to past threats that disable or bypass Microsoft Defender, such as previous malware and tools that register fake antivirus products to disable security features, increasing system vulnerability.
